comments: Finney-Smith (DAL) rests his hand on McCollum's (NOP) body and marginal contact occurs as he does not extend it or apply force during the driving shot attempt.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) slightly extends his right leg forward during the contest by Jones (NOP) and marginal foot to foot contact occurs after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) shot attempt ricochets off the rim and out of bounds without being touched by another player. Possession is correctly awarded to the Pelicans.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Bullock's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Finney-Smith (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Finney-Smith (DAL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Ingram's (NOP) driving shot attempt.
Ingram (NOP) does not lead unnaturally with his knee, as he immediately retracts it before coming together with Finney-Smith (DAL) during the driving shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) stops his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from Jones (NOP) and toward the perimeter.
Jones (NOP) legally contests Dinwiddie's (DAL) jump shot and cleanly blocks the shot attempt, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Jones (NOP) brings his off-arm toward Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and does not apply any force as marginal contact occurs during the layup attempt.
Jones (NOP) mutually engages with Dinwiddie (DAL) and neither player immediately disengages as a double personal foul is correctly called.
Dinwiddie (DAL) mutually engages with Jones (NOP) and neither player immediately disengages as a double personal foul is correctly called.
McCollum (NOP) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the pick is slipped.
McCollum (NOP) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Ingram (NOP) temporarily fumbles his dribble but does not bring his hand under the ball or to a pause before resuming his dribble.
Green (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position alongside Ingram (NOP) and absorbs the incidental contact at the end of the drive.
Green (DAL) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Marshall (NOP) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (DAL).
Dinwiddie (DAL) and McCollum (NOP) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Marshall (NOP) commits a take foul on Bullock (DAL).
Green (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Ingram (NOP) during the drive.
Jones (NOP) and Dinwiddie (DAL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.

Ingram (NOP) is in bounds when he deflects the throw-in, and then legally bats the ball back in bounds while airborne. Separately, the clock malfunctions, pausing momentarily at 4.9 and then running down to 3.4 seconds after play has stopped. [A clock malfunction is not reviewable unless it runs to 00:00 or separately as part of another replay review trigger.]
Jones (NOP) has his arm extended out while he moves in the same direction with Dinwiddie (DAL) and both players mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Jones (NOP) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (DAL).
Green (DAL) mutually engages and then disengages from Murphy III (NOP) to cleanly deflect the inbounds pass.
